<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Meeting the “Nicholson Challenge”</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from Gwyn Bevan (PEX 0004)</span></h1><h1 style="margin:24pt 0pt 0pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Meeting the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">“Nicholson Challenge”</span></h1><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A submission from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Gwyn Bevan</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Professor of Policy Analysis</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Department of Management</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">London School of Economics &amp; Political Science</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Summary</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Health Select Committee </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">argued</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to meet the  “Nicholson Challenge” </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the NHS in England </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">urgent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ly</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> need</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to develop </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">radically </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">different </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">strategy that will </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">enable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> transformational change through better coordinated care. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In this submission we outline </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">obstacles to developing such a strate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">gy and how these might be overcome by adopting the principles of a new approach</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, the Socio-Technical </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Allocation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of Resources</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">STAR</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">has been developed by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the Systems Modelling for Performance Optimisation and Service Equity (SyMPOSE</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">) research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> progra</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">mme </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">at LSE with funding by the Health Foundation. </span></li></ul><h2 style="margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The need for and obstacles to a strategy of transformational change</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The “Nicholson Challenge” is for the NHS in England to achieve 4% year-on-year efficiency gains to release resources to meet rising </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">demand for care without damaging the quality of care or health of populations.  The Health Select Committee in its 11th Report of the Session 2013-13  &lt;</span><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201213/cmselect/cmhealth/651/65102.htm"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://ww</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">w.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201213/cmselect/cmhealth/651/65102.htm</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&gt; summarized the progress that has been made by the English NHS in responding to that challenge to date. The Committee argued that there was an urgent need to move on from short-ter</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">m </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">salami slicing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of existing services within traditional provider and commissioner silos to a radically different strategy.  This strategy would be designed to enable transformational change through better coordinated care. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The NHS faces </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">two </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">obstacles in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">developing such a strategy</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Winning support from stakeholders.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">To be able to win support for such changes it is vital to involve stakeholders in a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">deliberative </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">process, and in particular to involve the patients and their carers who will be affected by su</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ch changes. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Although </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">NHS organisations </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are anxious about doing so, i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n our experience,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> its</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">downside risks are small and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">have been </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">far outweighed by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">two massive</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> potential benefits. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> First, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">requires providers to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">make </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">patients’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">interests </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">central to the ev</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">aluation of options</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  Second, involving  patients and carers in the development of strategic change means that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> as</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> their concerns are tackled from the start</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, this</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> improves the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> formulation of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> proposed change</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, informs how </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">an agreed change </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ought to be present</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed, and becomes one of its strongest selling points. </span></li></ol></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ol start="2" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Lack of data on the benefits of care</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o involve multiple stakeholders in a deliberative process of evaluating </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">strategies</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> requires three sets of data on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">each element in the care pathway</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">: the numbers of patients to be treated and the costs and benefits of treatment.  Systems of health care are designed to collect data on numbers and costs, but not benefits.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o invite stakeholders to assess options</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> for health care with</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">out data on benefits</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> would make a mockery of a process of deliberative decision </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">making.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We have developed various methods of estimating benefits by involving all stakeholders (including patients, carers and clinicians).  These </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">methods </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">vary in sophistication and the time </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">effort </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">required to produce judgemental estimates.  Our STAR process is backed up by visual and spreadsheet models which means that all stakeholders can see how these estimates give relative assessments of Value for Money (VfM) and also how these change whe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n subjected to sensitivity analysis.   </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">  </span></li></ol></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">How the STAR approach enables transformational change</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The guiding principles of the STAR approach are:</span></li><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It is designed to involve stakeholders in a deliberative process.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 68pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We provide guidance on the minimum data required and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">have developed methods for stakeholders to agree on estimates of the missing data of the benefits of each </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">element in the care pathway</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This is framed in terms of estimating the relative benefits from tr</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eatment of a typical patient, which together with the numbers treated give a visual comparison of the different scales of value from each option in rectangles of health gain. </span></li></ol><ol start="3" type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 67.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The estimates of value together with estimates of total costs are used to genera</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">te Value for Money (VfM) triangles that clearly indicate which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">elements in the care pathway</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are good and poor value for money and also their scale in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">consuming resources and contributing to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">value. These triangles are ordered from best to worst VfM in a vis</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ual display that signals that kinds of redistribution that ought to be explored: e.g., from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">elements </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">consume </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a material proportion of available resources but contribute little total value</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">; and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to options that can be increased in scale and have high Vf</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">M.</span></li></ol></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Health Foundation’s Report </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Looking for Value in Hard Times</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> &lt;</span><a href="http://www.health.org.uk/public/cms/75/76/313/3725/Looking%20for%20value%20in%20hard%20times.pdf?realName=P8KFa7.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.health.org.uk/public/cms/75/76/313/3725/Looking</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">%20for%20value%20in%20hard%20times.pdf?realName=P8KFa7.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&gt; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">gives a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">concise lucid </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">account of how the STAR approach was used in Sheffield PCT to change the pathway of care for women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">who suffer from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eating disorders</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. STAR showed that 80% of available reso</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">urces were used by an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">element </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that contributed only 13% of total benefits.  Stakeholders agreed that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">resources </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ought to be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">redistributed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and the PCT implemented a strategy that was estimated to reduce costs and improve outcomes for the population of women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">who suffer from eating disorders.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The SYMPOSE team worked with IMPRESS (Improving and Integrating Respiratory Services in the NHS -- Thinking strategically: Implementing locally &lt;</span><a href="http://www.impressresp.com/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.impressresp.com/</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&gt;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">) to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> help them distil the main findings of their own review on the cost-effectiveness of alternative treatments for Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD) for their commissioning guide issued in July 2012 &lt;</span><a href="http://www.impressresp.com/index.php?option=com_docman&amp;Itemid=82"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.impressresp.com/index.php?option=com_docman&amp;Itemid=82</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. The guide and the STAR approach has been the subject of high praise in a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">BMJ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> editorial by Sir Muir Gray &lt;</span><a href="http://www.bmj.com/content/345/bmj.e6192"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.bmj.com/content/345/bmj.e6192</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&gt;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Health Foundation has funded the development of the STAR approach into a user-friendly decision support tool</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> (this can be downloaded at </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">http://www.health.org.uk/areas-of-work/star/star-online-demonstrati</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on/the-star-tool/). The use of the STAR tool </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">with three CCGs (Gloucestershire, Tower Hamlets and East Sussex)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> was evaluated by th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e SyMPOSE team and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">we </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">found that the greatest contribution of the STAR approach was on four criteria: </span></li></ol><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">capacity to use health e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">conomic evidence (e.g. cost-effectiveness information) in its decision making; </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">quality of the process for involving all key stakeholders (clinicians, managers, patients) in setting priorities to find resources to finance improvements in the prevention;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.33pt; padding-left:4.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">es</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tablishing a  process to ensure the way resources are targeted is based on relevant criteria, which are publicly accessible and can be challenged; and </span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 50pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">making good use of available data and evidence and soundly deriving estimates where such data and eviden</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ce are not available.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We see the STAR tool as providing a way for those who want to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">lead transformational</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> change to work out the data they need, estimate the data that are missing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> by working in a process of deliberative decision making involving stakeholders</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to formulate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">strategies </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">where effort ought to be directed most fruitfully in implementing such changes.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>